INSERT INTO `staff` VALUES (2,'MacCorkle','Lyn','Digital Repository Librarian','284-4143',126,0,'lmaccork@miami.edu','',0,1,'43b242873b608e78aa426484060b1473',1,'talkback|faq|librarian|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','<p>Lyn  MacCorkle joined the faculty of the University of Miami Libraries in 1973.</p> <p>She  is currently a member the Digital Initiatives Department  and is  responsible for  developing and maintaining digital projects and  the  supporting repository  infrastructure.&nbsp; Recently she  collaborated  with  University faculty to design and create several University of   Miami  Libraries Digital Fellows projects.&nbsp;  During the last year she   developed the Digital Initiatives web site, and  implemented the   CONTENTdm digital repository in support of a sponsored project  funded   by the State of Florida.&nbsp;  Beginning in spring 2007, with the   collaboration of the Graduate School,  she implemented the web and   database infrastructure for an electronic  dissertations and theses   (ETD) service.</p> <p>Before  joining the Digital Initiatives Department in 2002,  she  served at different  times as ICPSR representative; the  bibliographer  for sociology and psychology;  web development librarian;  the head of  the computer assisted research services,  and the manager of  a  microcomputer laboratory. &nbsp;She has participated on a number of   University  of Miami Committees, including the Faculty Senate, the World   Wide Web  Committee, and the Computer Networking Security Committee.</p> <p>Dr.  MacCorkle received her M.L.S. from George Peabody  College and  her Ph.D. in  Library and Information Studies from Florida  State. &nbsp;She  is a member of The American Society for  Information Science  &amp;  Technology, and the American Association for History and  Computing. &nbsp;In  the last several years, she has given  presentations on  faculty  collaboration and library digitization projects at  professional   meetings. &nbsp;Her interests include  digitizing and describing cultural   heritage materials; faculty communication;  technologies for digital   preservation and delivery of teaching and scholarly resources;    usability and other issues related to presentation.</p> <p>Travel, Tourism and Urban Growth in Greater Miami, 2006 <a href=\"http://scholar.library.miami.edu/miamidigital/\">http://scholar.library.miami.edu/miamidigital/</a></p> <p>Cuban/Latino Theater Archive, 2006<br /> <a href=\"http://scholar.library.miami.edu/archivoteatral/\">http://scholar.library.miami.edu/archivoteatral/</a></p> <p>UM Faculty Publications Database, 2002<br /> <a href=\"http://scholar.library.miami.edu/facpubs02/\">http://scholar.library.miami.edu/facpubs02/</a></p> <p>&quot;The Sixties&quot;, 2004<br /> <a href=\"http://scholar.library.miami.edu/sixties/\">http://scholar.library.miami.edu/sixties/</a></p>','','Associate Professor','',104,'John MacCorkle','Brother','305-344-5600','5023 Southwest 59th Avenue','Miami,','FL','33155','000-000-0000','786-253-9240','305-284-4027','74','25.723781,-80.289969',47.6666,135.666,2,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(9,'Beiro','Roca','Facilities Manager','284-8440',132,0,'rbeiro@miami.edu','',0,1,'de3cb66437722ab69d8a26da32c59183',1,'talkback|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Building Facility Coordinator','101C',316,'Roca M. Novo','Daughter','305-733-9872','9471 Southwest 31st Terrace','Miami,','FL','33165','305-552-8920','305-281-4499','305-284-4027','11','25.740934,-80.349419',42.4529,36.6929,2,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(13,'Heath','Gary','Systems Support Technician','284-4056',129,0,'gheath@miami.edu','',0,1,NULL,1,'','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Sr. Help Desk Technician','320',76,'Sabrina Heath','Daughter','305-528-2277','11940 Southwest 188th Terrace','Miami, ','FL','33177','305-527-2622','305-804-4827','305-284-4027','96','25.592186,-80.386033',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(17,'Yordan','Alexis','Senior Financial Analyst','284-6776',101,0,'ayordan@miami.edu','',0,1,'cad4a0845b06232e4896c5e08b544dce',1,'admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Sr. Financial Analyst','333',316,'Maria Elena Yordan','Mother','786-253-1553','601 Northeast 22nd Street, Apartment #32','Miami,','FL','33137','','786-493-3877','305-284-4027','29','25.7983685,-80.1867609',51.533,56.383,2,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(18,'Zavac','Nancy','Head, Music Library','284-9884',103,1,'nzavac@miami.edu','',0,1,'745562839910cc56575bfbf7403657d0',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','<p>Nancy Zavac, Head of the Marta and Austin Weeks Music Library, has a Master&#39;s of Music degree in Musicology from the University of Miami, and a Master&#39;s of Science degree in Library Science from Florida State University.&nbsp; From 1979 to 1982 she worked as a Music Cataloger at the University of Miami Music Library and from 1982 to present she has served as Head of the Weeks Music Library.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The highlight of her career was the move to the new Weeks Music Library facility in January 2005.&nbsp; Another milestone was the acquisition of the Larry Taylor-Billy Matthews Musical Theatre Archive in 1991.&nbsp; As Head of the Weeks Music Library Ms. Zavac is responsible for the administration and management of the library to include selection of music materials and electronic resources, information services, bibliographic instruction, cataloging, and the supervision of library&rsquo;s professional and support staff.&nbsp; Nancy also teaches a 3 credit course in Music Bibliography and regularly serves on theses committees for graduate students.&nbsp; She is an active member of the Music Library Association, Southeast Chapter of the Music Library Association, and the Music OCLC Users Group.&nbsp; As a member of the MLA Education Committee she has planned several &ldquo;Continuing Education Forums&rdquo; for national meetings.</p>\r\n','','Librarian Associate Professor','107 Weeks Music Library',431,'Jeffrey Zavac','Husband','305-213-8907