 Head of the Information Resource Center for the School of Business. &nbsp;Her previous job experiences include company analysis, programming, and recruitment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms. Jui&rsquo;s teaching and research interests are in the fields of e-research tools in competitive intelligence and market research.&nbsp; Her consulting work with organizations has focused on business planning, research strategies, and program development.&nbsp; She holds both a M.L.I.S. from the University of South Florida and a M.B.A. from the University of Miami.&nbsp; As the Gold Fund Endowment Librarian, her primary responsibility is to the students and faculty of the School of Business Administration, and as Head of the Information Resource Center, she is responsible for the administration and management of operations for the Center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She has represented the Libraries&rsquo; interests in university-wide committees such as ITAC, General Welfare, and the Faculty Senate.&nbsp; Currently, she is a member of the university&#39;s Women &amp; Minorities committee.&nbsp; She is a member of the American Library Association (ALA) and Special Libraries Association (SLA).&nbsp; In addition to her service to the University and profession, she has served as an Advisory Board Member for electronic products to both Standard &amp; Poor&rsquo;s and Thomson Gale Group.</p>\r\n','','Librarian Associate Professor','AGB 400',431,'Julio Jui','Father','305-266-2410','6131 Southwest 17th Street','Miami,','FL','33155','305-269-1819','305-790-3652','000-000-0000','','25.754972,-80.294599',46.643,52.5529,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(36,'Cruz','Leela M.','Monographic Copy Cataloger/Receiving Assistant','284-4726',106,0,'lmcruz@miami.edu','',0,1,NULL,1,'','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Library Assistant','',404,'Nelson Cruz','Husband','305-235-2436','9735 Southwest 210th Terrace','Miami,','FL','33189','305-235-2436','305-979-1360','305-284-4234','47','25.571575,-80.3482159',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(39,'Puentes','Cel