ociety of North American (ARLIS/NA), and the Association of Jewish Libraries (AJL).&nbsp; In AJL she served at the national level as Vice President for Membership, Editor of their online newsletter, and Program Chair for the national convention.&nbsp; Locally she served as President of the South Florida chapter of AJL. &nbsp;Ms. Robarts has been serving as a consultant to the Temple Judea Library in Coral Gables and is actively involved in its current renovation and reorganization.</p>\r\n','','Art &amp; Art History, Classics, Judaic Studies, Religious Studies Librarian and Theatre Arts ','',352,'Evan Robarts','Son','646-812-8371','2120 Sunset Drive, Sunset Island Four','Miami Beach,','FL','33140','305-538-3888','305-318-0376','305-284-4027','36','25.8176795,-80.1372757',26.5564,138.332,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(140,'Clark','Angela','RSMAS Librarian, Marine Science','421-4020',119,1,'a.clark@miami.edu','',0,1,'be5afb89b1b54fb435831c9080eadfee',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','<p>Angela Clark has worked in academic libraries for over twenty years.&nbsp; She has a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Psychology from Georgia State University and received her Master&rsquo;s in Library and Information Science from Simmons College in Boston, Massachusetts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She joined the faculty of the University of Miami Libraries in 2004 as a Librarian Assistant Professor at the Rosenstiel School of Marine and Atmospheric Science Library on Key Biscayne.&nbsp; Before coming to the University of Miami, she was the Assistant Department Head of Access Services at the University of Georgia Libraries in Athens, 2001-2004.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Angela is a member of Oasis Christian Ministries International, and serves on the board of directors for the Oasis Enhancement Center.</p>\r\n','','Librarian Associate Professor','SLAB 167A',261,'Michael Hughes','Husband','305-336-6183','13335 Northwest 17th Court','Miami,','FL','33167','305-681-4268','305-297-4864','305-361-9306',