ss\": \"basic\"}','','003468','Sr. Library Assistant','',404,'Rajakumar Gopal','Husband','352-328-1779','1441 Northwest 19th Street, Apartment #109','Miami,','FL','33125','305-545-9598','352-328-1778','000-000-0000','','25.7931176,-80.220109',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(227,'Cooper','Yolanda','Acting Dean &amp; University Librarian ','284-3551',101,1,'ycooper@miami.edu','',0,1,'45f11a64843b6a5528842f5033825031',0,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|view_map','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','Yolanda Cooper joined the faculty of the University of Miami Libraries in 2006 as the Deputy University Librarian. &nbsp;Yolanda provides leadership and oversight in the planning, management, and day-to-day operations of the University of Miami Libraries to include the Otto G. Richter Library, Marta &amp; Austin Weeks Music Library, the Paul Buisson Architecture Library, the Business Information Resource Center, the Rosenstiel School of Marine and Atmospheric Science Library, Digital Programs, Access Information, and Research Services, Special Collections, the Cuban Heritage Collection, and Information Management and Systems.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPrior to joining the University of Miami Libraries, Yolanda served as the Associate University Librarian for Organizational Development at the University of Virginia Library in Charlottesville, Virginia from 2003 to 2006, responsible for Human Resources, Business Services, Management Information Services, Grants, and Fiscal Administration. Prior to that, she was the Assistant Dean for Human Resources and Assistant to the Dean at Indiana University Bloomington Libraries from 1994 to 2003; from 1990 to 1994 at the University of Northern Colorado, Michener Library in technical services; and from 1979 to 1990 at the University of Illinois Library focusing mainly on technical services operations, and information technology.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYolanda holds a B.G.S. and a M.L.S. from Indiana University. &nbsp;In 2004 she was selected to attend the FRYE Institute in Atlanta, Georgia, and participate as a FRYE Fellow. &nbsp;Her professional interests are in Organization Development, Data Curation, Digital Libraries, and Diversity in Higher Education. Yolanda has presented and developed training programs focused on diversity in libraries, web development, organization development, change and transition management, leadership, fiscal management, organizational assessment strategies, and Worklife.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYolanda is a member of the American Library Association (ALA), the Association of College and Research Libraries (ACRL), the Black Caucus of the American Library Association (BCALA), Library Administration and Management Association (LAMA), and the Society of American Archivists (SAA). &nbsp;She has participated on the ALA Committee for Diversity, co-moderated the Diversity Interest Network Exchange, chaired the ALA Committee on Organization, and participated on the ALA/ACRL Presidents Program Committee. &nbsp;She is a member of the University of Miami Information Technology Leadership Council, ex-officio member of the Graduate Council, is a member of the Africana Studies Board, the Center for Latin American Studies Board, Vice President of the Williams, Woodson, Marshall Association (WWMA), and the Chair of the Faculty Senate Committee on Women and Minorities.','030991','Librarian Associate Professor','',NULL,'Resha','Daughter','305-989-2052','7803 Southwest 100th Street','Miami,','FL','33156','305-595-4035','305-984-3165','305-284-4027','','25.677747,-80.32113',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(228,'Jean','Elisiene','Circulation &amp; Reserves Assistant, Architecture Library','284-5282',117,0,'ejean@miami.edu','',0,1,NULL,1,'','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','<br />','','Sr. Library Assistant','',306,'Ursula Harris','Friend','305-804-6265','1392 Northwest 31st Street','Miami,','FL','33142','305-633-5726','786-267-3292','000-000-0000','10','25.809808,-80.2041799',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(229,'Abraham','Maira','Assistant to the Deputy University