Information Studies from the University of Rhode Island.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following an internship at Brown University, Mr. Renaud joined the University of Miami Libraries in 2002 as Education and Psychology Librarian. &nbsp;While at the Libraries, John has been the Electronic Resources Librarian, Assistant Director of Collection Development, and Head of Acquisitions. He currently serves as Director of Collection Strategies and Scholarly Communication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John has served on the Teaching Methods Committee of the Association of College and Research Libraries and is currently a member of the Library Administration and Management Division of the American Library Association, where he serves on the Financial Advancement and Management Practices committees. He is the libraries&rsquo; representative to the NERL consortia and serves on the Springer Library Advisory Board. His areas of professional interest are the impact of journal and electronic resource price structures on library collections, the long term costs of maintaining different types of library collections, preservation of electronic collections, and the development and support of alternative, sustainable modes of scholarly communication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>John represents the Libraries on the University of Miami Faculty Senate. He has served as United Way Ambassador for the Libraries and is part of the Libraries&rsquo; team in the annual Corporate Run to Benefit the Leukemia and Lymphoma Society.</p>\r\n','','Librarian Associate Professor','338',167,'Louis Moohchan-Jaen','Domestic Partner','305-498-7222','401 69th Street, No. 701','Miami Beach,','FL','33141','000-000-0000','786-473-9524','000-000-0000','','25.854578,-80.122735',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(302,'Arguello','Clarisa','Daytime Circulation Supervisor and Reserves Coordinator','284-3234',99,0,'carguello@miami.edu','',0,1,'de2e1539cdf338b35f2a133d34dcfc3c',0,'','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Daytime Circulation Supervisor and Reserves Coordinator','',446,'Clarisa Herdocia','Mother','305-586-4352','680 Northwest 133rd Court','Miami,','FL','33182','','305-984-1689','000-000-0000','','25.773845,-80.412077',14.8,4.64,2,1.25,1.25,NULL),(306,'Santana','Gilda','Head, Architecture Library','284-5282',117,1,'gsantana@miami.edu','',0,1,'dbb14b5a3e7448e35c08f6ca0a135a1b',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','<p>Gilda Santana has worked in academic libraries and museums, and in art galleries.&nbsp; She received her Master&rsquo;s in Library and Information Science from Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She joined the faculty of the University of Miami Libraries in 2007 as Head of Architecture Information and Resources, which serves the School of Architecture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms. Santana is a member of the Association of Architecture School Librarians (AASL), Art Libraries Association of North America (ARLIS), the Visual Resources Association (VRA), the Society of Architectural Historians (SAH), and the Latin American Studies Association (LASA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Her research interests focus on the impact of technology in visual resources with an emphasis on the disciplines of Architecture and Art History.</p>\r\n','','Librarian Associate Professor','',431,'Janet Gavarrete','Relative','305-665-7913','2974 Bird Ave., #17, ','Miami,','FL','33133','000-000-0000','305-490-0365','000-000-0000','','25.734911,-80.2414',41.1663,128.909,2,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(307,'Chaparro','Alvaro','Evening Circulation Supervisor','284-4811',99,0,'achaparro@miami.edu','',0,1,NULL,1,'supervisor','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Library Supervisor','',307,'Leidy Marino','Wife','786-278-0749','8290 Lake Drive, Apartment #510','Doral,','FL','33166','','305-206-3686','000-000-0000','','25.8179961,-80.3308074',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(311,'Figueroa','Manuel','Interlibrary Loan Lending Assistant','284-6102',113,0,'m.figueroa3@miami.edu','',0,1,NULL,0,'','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Sr. Library Assistant','',23