-0000','','25.74395,-80.391036',26.98,28.65,1,1.25,1.25,NULL),(349,'Reinke','Scott','Preservation Administrator ','284-1844 ',128,1,'s.reinke@miami.edu','',0,1,'6fd34bb226c40dea76d4a8d516cd3d8e',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','<p>Scott Reinke joined the University of Miami Libraries&nbsp;as the Preservation Administrator in March 2010. He is responsible for developing and managing a comprehensive preservation program that supports&nbsp;the Special Collections, Cuban Heritage Collection, University Archives, and Digital Initiatives. Additional responsibilities include managing a&nbsp;conservation lab,&nbsp;disaster planning, environmental monitoring, integrated pest management, general collections care, exhibition&nbsp;preparation, preservation condition surveys, bindery operations,&nbsp;and community outreach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scott earned&nbsp;a MLIS from the University of Southern Mississippi and a B.A.&nbsp;in Anthropology from the University of Hawaii at Manoa. He held previous positions at the National Archives and Records Administration in St.&nbsp;Louis&nbsp;and at the University of Hawaii at Manoa Libraries.</p>\r\n','','Librarian Assistant Professor','301H',261,'Laura Capell','Spouse','305-803-0847','690 Southwest 1st Court, Apartment #2319','Miami,','FL','33130','','305-803-0915','000-000-0000','','25.767895,-80.196224',19.5129,58.5129,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(351,'Creque','Michelle ','Stacks Supervisor','284-3235',99,0,'m.hernandez27@miami.edu','',0,1,NULL,1,'supervisor','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','','','Library Supervisor','',446,'Cameron Creque','Husband','786-286-8191','9340 Haitian Drive','Cutler Bay, ','FL','33189','000-000-0000','786-449-5748','000-000-0000','','25.5836553,-80.3427874',0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(352,'Stoute','Anna','Head of Education &amp; Outreach','284-6027',118,1,'astoute@miami.edu','',0,1,'57f3ad74fa37a15701799b7f084ac692',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','Anna Stoute is the Head of Education and Outreach for the University of Miami Libraries. She provides leadership and innovation in the development and provision of library education services and outreach activities. As Head of E&amp;O she directly supervises the E&amp;O faculty, staff, and student assistants. She collaborates with the college and school libraries to provide a comprehensive education and outreach program in alignment with the goals of the Libraries and the University.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSince joining UM in 2010, she has worked with various departments on campus to increase research support for graduate students and faculty. She is a co-founder of the Dissertation Writing Group (DWG) a program developed in collaboration with the Graduate School and the Writing Center. She is also the co-facilitator for the University of Miami&rsquo;s Quality Enhancement Plan (QEP): Faculty Learning Communities to Enhance Undergraduate Education: with an Initial Focus on Information, Communication, and Technology Literacy.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPrior to her role with the Libraries, she joined the Allyn &amp; Betty Taylor Library, University Western of Ontario as the Head, Research and Instructional Services where she served as co-investigator for the libraries&rsquo; LIBQUAL survey. In 2006 Anna became the Head Librarian for Macdonald Campus Library, McGill University; she was instrumental in the development and implementation of a required undergraduate literacy course.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter graduating with her Masters in Library and Information Studies from McGill University in 2002, Anna became the Instruction Librarian for Macdonald Campus Library. She developed the orientation and instruction programs for undergraduates and graduate students in the Faculty of Agriculture and Environmental Sciences. She was active in the Canadian Library Association, as the President of the Montreal Chapter, later becoming a member of the Executive Board CLA Standing Committee on Research and Development.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAnna is a member of the American Library Association (ALA), and the Association of College and Research Libraries (ACRL). She is a member of the Conference Committee for the annual Information Fluency Conference. Anna is on the Advisory Committee on Teaching and Learning (ACTL), EDUCAUSE. She has presented at the Information Fluency Conference, the Southeastern Writing Center (SWCA) Conference, as well as the ACRL Spring Virtual Institute','39820','Librarian Associate Professor','',431,'Jacqueline Stoute','Mother','514-364-1660','1100 Northeast 116th Street','Biscayne Park,','FL','33161','','305-469-5388','000-000-0000','','25.882132,-80.17599',20.6929,49.0729,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(354,'Strickland','Amy','Music Librarian','284-1895',103,0,'a.strickland@miami.edu','',0,1,'fa04e3f634c989618c6cc47cac1e0d1d',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','Amy Strickland received her Master&rsquo;s degree in Library and Information  Studies from the University of Alabama, where she also received a  Master&rsquo;s degree in Music, specializing in musicology. <br /><br />In May  2010 Ms. Strickland joined Weeks Music Library, where she oversees  cataloging, digital, and web services, and assists in education and  outreach activities. She has participated in a variety of library  initiatives, including the implementation of the Variations streaming  audio reserve system.<br /><br />Ms. Strickland is a member of the American  Library Association (ALA), the Music Library Association (MLA), the  Music Library Association&rsquo;s Southeast Chapter (SEMLA), and the Music  OCLC Users Group (MOUG). She presented at the 2011 annual meeting of the  Music Library Association&rsquo;s Southeast Chapter, where she discussed the  University of Miami Libraries&rsquo; implementation of Variations. <br /><br />Ms.  Strickland&rsquo;s research interests include the performing practices of  modern and avant garde music, the effects of changing copyright laws on  libraries, and the adoption of new technologies to enhance library  services. <br /><br />','32232','Librarian Assistant Professor','106',18,'Bill or Mary Strickland','Parents','256-878-3466','5325 Southwest 77th Court, Apartment #206F','Miami, ','FL','33155','305-595-6426','256-572-3404','000-000-0000','','25.719503,-80.319695',28.7029,63.1029,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(356,'Capell','Laura','Head of Digital Production &amp; Electronic Records Archivist','284-9328',110,1,'l.capell@miami.edu','',0,1,'5c0993398150f21ad3918bda1be454fd',1,'talkback|faq|records|librarian|supervisor|admin_calendar','{\"css\": \"basic\"}','Laura Capell joined the faculty in 2011, and is currently serving as the Head of Digital Production &amp; Electronic Records Archivist.&nbsp; She is responsible for managing digital projects for special collections materials and for coordinating the Libraries&rsquo; electronic records archiving initiatives. She held pervious positions as the Digital Archivist at the University of Southern Mississippi and as a Project Archivist at the University of Hawaii. She also worked as a Senior Archivist at the Georgia Archives.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMs. Capell received her M.S.L.S. from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill and her M.A. in Public History from North Carolina State University. She holds Bachelor&rsquo;s degrees in history and German from Auburn University. She is also a Certified Archivist.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMs. Capell is a member of the Society of American Archivists, and the Society of Florida Archivists.&nbsp; Her research interests include enhancing access to archival materials through description and digitization.','','Librarian Assistant Professor','',104,'Scott Reinke','Husband','305-803-0915','690 Southwest 1st Court, Apartment #2319','Miami,','FL','33130','000-000-0000','305-803-0847','000-000-0000','','25.767895,-80.196224',14.713,37.8929,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(357,