 Book from the Corcoran College of Art and Design in 2013.&nbsp; She held previous positions as a Cataloging Consultant for the Free Library of Philadelphia&rsquo;s Rare Book Department, and as Assistant Archivist and Librarian for The Barnes Foundation. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nMs. O&rsquo;Dell is an active member of the <a href=\"http://rbms.info/\">Rare Books and Manuscripts Section</a> of the Association of College and Research Libraries, where she currently works with the Bibliographic Standards Committee and the Publications and Communications Committee.&nbsp; She is involved in a collaborative project with the&nbsp;Art Libraries Society of North America to create the <a href=\"http://arlisnabookartsig.blogspot.com/2014/07/fantastic-resource-demo-release-arlisna.html\"><em>Artists&#39; Books Thesaurus</em></a>. &nbsp;In the Miami community, Ms. O&#39;Dell is Co-Leader for the local chapter of <a href=\"http://girldevelopit.com/chapters/miami\">Girl Develop It</a>, a nonprofit organization that empowers women of diverse backgrounds to learn software and Web development skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHer research focuses on assessment and manipulation of library catalog data to forward study of the book as object.&nbsp; She has spoken on various topics surrounding education and strategies for enhanced library cataloging activity. &nbsp;Recently, she investigated the re-invigoration of provenance and creator metadata in library catalogs, the bibliographic description of zines, and appropriate subject metadata for special collections.','','Special Collections Cataloger','',404,'Pamela O&#039;Dell','Mother','301-937-2799','2263 SW 37th Ave #624','Miami ','FL','33145','','240-393-2421','305-284-4721','','25.7488106,-80.2543015',14.673,12.723,0,1.83333,1.83333,NULL),(421,'Ortiz-Rosado','Alexandria','E-Resources Sr. Library Assistant','284-4586',100,0,'a.ortizrosado@miami.edu',NULL,NULL,1,'c551d46afac720d65bebcd7bd46b58f8',1,'',NULL,'','','Library Assistant','',79,'Myrta